0","line":2},{"title":"A Short History of Reconstruction (Updated Edition)","target":"https://amzn.to/3Huw7Xn","line":3},{"title":"A Fever in the Heartland: The Ku Klux Klan's Plan to Take Over American, and the Woman Who Stopped Them","target":"https://amzn.to/3H8bwrU","line":4},{"title":"Klan War: Ulysses S. Grant and the Battle to Save Reconstruction","target":"https://amzn.to/4oskRLO","line":5},{"title":"Black Reconstruction in America, 1860-1880","target":"https://amzn.to/4ovzONe","line":6},{"title":"Stony the Road: Reconstruction, White Supremacy, and the Rise of Jim Crow","target":"https://amzn.to/45rL98l","line":7},{"title":"I Saw Death Coming: A History of Terror and Survival in the War Against Reconstruction","target":"https://amzn.to/4liTKA0","line":8},{"title":"The Second Founding: How the Civil War and Reconstruction Remade the Constitution","target":"https://amzn.to/4mFYqRL","line":9},{"title":"The Rise and Fall of the Second American Republic: Reconstruction, 1860-1920","target":"https://amzn.to/3Hq3uuq","line":10},{"title":"The Republic for Which It Stands: The United States During Reconstruction and the Gilded Age, 1865-1896","target":"https://amzn.to/3Ja7UpM","line":11}],"class_name":"SmartBlock","last_embed":{"hash":"1hlhml5","at":1754841203957}},
